Most of the time, the issue is resolved by an apology.
Before you go on to make a mocking explanation, it is worthwhile to meditate on the things you can do to make your colleagues' lives bitter and to make a conscious effort to avoid them.
You borrow something that's not yours?
There's nothing more irritating than when you want to grab a document, an office tool or your phone and you can't find them.
Do you remember yesterday you put the stapler on the table, but by this morning it was gone?
Do you find your pen lost on one of your colleagues' desk?
Do not take anything from your colleagues without asking, for they will rightly be angry with you for taking their things.
Do not take envelopes or post-it from the office because it may be unpleasant when you need them immediately and they run out before time.
You gossip about your colleagues' private lives?
There's no good solution to stop rumors that are already running.
Who, what is he doing and with whom?
Where and why?
Do not pass on to everyone the information (conjectures) you have about the private lives of your colleagues!
Do not abuse your colleague's trust when he shares his innermost secrets with you!
Bury what you have heard in yourself and do not gossip about your colleague in his absence, even though others also know things about him.
You're taking unjustified sick leave?
When you call the office and say that you are sick and have an unbearable headache, you feel bad or you feel that you would rather rest that day; think that others must do your work, your unfinished tasks, your work by term.
Don't bother your colleague!
If you know in advance that you will not be in the office the next day or something may happen to you, so you must stay at home, tell them so that your colleagues or your boss do not have to face your absence the next day.
Screams, laughs, phone calls
You're in your job, but you're suddenly taken off by the laughter of your colleagues?
Have you unintentionally overheard a telephone conversation that you would have been better off not to hear?
Do not disturb your colleagues with your murmurs, songs, loud conversations (less when you do them above their head), patting, constant blasphemies, expressing your discontent aloud.
All of these can be annoying, even if you're not currently delving into a project (writing, planning, organizing).
Do you blame others for a mistake?
Don't blame others if you haven't finished something in time, you forgot to send an important letter or message!
You don't mean the chaos that eventually reigns in the office, or the noise that your colleagues make!
You must recognize if you have made a mistake that hurts others and you must make amends!
Ask how you can make up for your lack!
Do you feel too at home at the office?
Jogging and slippers: a very comfortable habit for the home, but not suitable for the office!
Don't wear a comfortable jogging suit even if your occupation allows it!
Don't be disorganized, respect your colleagues and yourself by wearing everyday, elegant and beautiful clothes when your occupation demands it!
You lose interest if you want to live up to the public's expectations.
