Six hundred thousand drivers were passed the date and therefore did not manage to change their old driving licence which expires at the end of the year.
Today is the last day people can apply for the change so officials give them until the end of the year to issue the new card.
However, the Ministry is not afraid that after the New Year hundreds of thousands of drivers will be on the roads without a valid carnet.
According to traffic, the license has not been changed mainly by those who no longer even want to drive.
While in towns they announce a rapid decline in the change of cards, the metropolis offices are full of applications and interest in the new card has increased.
City Hall estimates about 2,000 customers a day.
The queues are for half an hour.
In Prague, about 140,000 drivers have not yet obtained their new driving licence.
The issuing of a new card takes 20 days.
However, you can apply for a card within a shorter period of five days.
But in that case the driver must pay five hundred crowns.
Drivers who are required to change their pass and do not arrive until the end of the year, but will be on the roads without the valid pass, will risk a fine from January.
The offender will pay a maximum of two thousand crowns.
The police can fix the infraction with a warning.
If it is an administrative offence, the fine is 2,500 crowns.
According to the above information, a person who does not go anywhere could be fined.
