Governments may reach a turning point after they are unable to govern.
People don't believe them as politicians, but they usually suspend their disbelief when a new batch takes over.
Once it's clear that the prime minister can't make things better, that he doesn't have much time left, that suspension is too much: public officials start to fail; cabinet ministers get exposed; the press seeks bad news; and the government gets defensive and doesn't focus.
